OL,3,CSenior police officer sacked for
OL,4,Cpunching two women
OL,6,FSuperintendent Mark Edgington, head of
OL,7,FPSD, said: "The burden of proof
OL,8,Frequired for a criminal prosecution
OL,9,Fand misconduct to be proven is
OL,10,Fdifferent.
OL,12,F"The panel reached its decision that
OL,13,FInspector Munro assaulted the two
OL,14,Fwomen on the balance of probabilities
OL,15,Fhaving heard the evidence presented to
OL,16,Fthem.
OL,18,F"A criminal conviction requires
OL,19,Fallegations to be proved beyond all
OL,20,Freasonable doubt, and the difference
OL,21,Fbetween those levels is significant.
